data.name: High Dramma Returns to the Walking Fish Theatre!
data.caption: High Dramma Returns to the Walking Fish Theatre!
data.description:
It's been a long time comin', but after months of white hot anticipation, @[195967877193581:274:High Dramma] will be returning to the @[71972094780:274:Walking Fish Theatre] in Philadelphia for a 3-night performance of their all-new sketch-comedy show!

The show starts at 8PM. Tickets are $10 at the door on Friday and Saturday, and Thursday is Pay What You Want!

data.message: So in addition to being a part of the Montreal and Charm City Comedy Festival's this month, we're excited to announce that we'll be performing our first all-new show of the year, which will run from May 14th-16th at The Walking Fish Theatre! More details to come….so keep an eye out for the invite!

And we have another confirmation! High Dramma is proud to announce we'll be heading up north next month to be a part of the  10th Annual Montreal Sketchfest! We'll be announcing dates soon, so please check back! - http://montrealsketchfest.com/

data.caption: ManDudeBro With High Dramma!
data.description:
It's a collision of sketch and improv comedy as Lehigh Valley-based improv heroes Mandudebro team up with Philadelphia-based sketch heroes High Dramma!

What's scripted? What's made up? Who knows?!

Actually... we all know. Mandudebro will be performing a set of longform improv comedy and High Dramma will be doing a set of hilarious sketches. Glad we cleared that up.

High Dramma is Jackie Wolfson, DC Fisher, Curt Riedy, and Sarah Braun. There's also some fine, fine banjo playing by Pete Heleva. - www.highdramma.com

Mandudebro is Matt Candio, Jon Lunger, Dan Maher and Evan Stutts. - www.mandudebro.com

Tonight at 9PM - Head to the Philly Improv Theater (PHIT) to watch Curt from High Dramma lead a group of very funny Philadelphians as they face off against 2 other groups on stage in Iron Sketch, an epic battle of sketch comedy!
data.name: Sketch Comedy: IRON SKETCH BATTLE - WATER
data.caption: Sketch Comedy: IRON SKETCH BATTLE - WATER
data.description:
"The Chairman" invites YOU to bear witness as three sketch comedy groups perform for our amazingly talented, special guest judges. This month's guests include;

Darryl Charles - Stand-up comedian, Host of "DTF - The Darryl & Timaree Fun Hour", and improvisor at ComedySportz Philadelphia!

Kristen Schier - Member of PHIT Improv House Team, "The Future" and one-half of both the "The Kristen & Amie Show" and "The Wadsworth Constant".

PLUS!  Special guest judge, professional wrestler for Chikara Pro Wrestling, Ophidian Cobra!

Here is a breakdown of July's competitors in alphabetical order by Team;

"Braised Stakes"
Mentor - Curt Riedy of High Dramma
Pim Van Huijelom
Jack O'Keeffe
Courtney Painter
David Piccolomini

"River Milk"
Mentor - Sam Narisi of Camp Woods / "Fear Town, USA"
Patric Ciervo 
Jolie Darrow 
Tom Hannigan 
Alvaro Lopez-Moreno

"Ali Vaziri"
Mentor - Rob Baniewicz of Dog Mountain / Alley of Nightmares
Lizzie Burrows 
Josh Higham 
Emily Moore 
Max Sittenfield 

Think you know who's going to win? Comment below and show your support by spreading the word!

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Iron Sketch is a monthly, competitive sketch show hosted by The Chairman for Philly Improv Theater every 1st Thursday at 9pm ($8 advance / $10 door)

"The Chairman” opens Iron Sketch to anyone provided they will pledge their time & efforts over a single month to writing, producing, and performing ten minutes of original, sketch comedy. Each contestant will be asked to collaborate with randomly assigned teammates and will work under the supervision & direction of a mentor.

Each month, twelve respondents will be randomly picked & divided into groups of three. The groups will then have a month to write and develop their show with their assigned mentor. The teams then present their shows to a live audience and star-studded panel of judges!

Sign up by emailing ironsketch@phillyimprovtheater.com

data.name: FINAL NIGHT! High Dramma Has a Comedy Show This Week.
data.caption: FINAL NIGHT! High Dramma Has a Comedy Show This Week.
data.description:
High Dramma, that sketch troupe your one friend is in, has that show in April that you said you'd probably check out!

That's right, High Dramma returns to the Walking Fish for their first new show in almost a full year! After stops at the Philly, Montreal and New York City Sketchfests,your favorite Fishtown-based sketch comedy group is back at its home base for a show chock full of new sketches. Shows are on Wed, 4/23, Thurs, 4/24, Fri, 4/25 & Sat, 4/26, all at 8 PM at the Walking Fish Theater, so you've got plenty of chances to indulge in our unique mix of highbrow vulgarity and lowbrow cleverness.

Purchase Tickets Here - http://www.walkingfishtheatre.com
